            "html": "<strong>11. Step 11: 3. Removing Tea Stains</strong><div class='step-images count-4'><figure><img src='https://content.instructables.com/FMI/1Z6R/KX4OUXRA/FMI1Z6RKX4OUXRA.jpg?auto=webp&fit=bounds&frame=1auto=webp&frame=1&height=300&auto=webp&fit=bounds&width=600&height=450&quality=75' alt='3. Removing Tea Stains' loading='lazy'></figure><figure><img src='https://content.instructables.com/FGP/RVG6/KX4OUXRB/FGPRVG6KX4OUXRB.jpg?auto=webp&fit=bounds&frame=1auto=webp&frame=1&height=300&auto=webp&fit=bounds&width=600&height=450&quality=75' alt='3. Removing Tea Stains' loading='lazy'></figure><figure><img src='https://content.instructables.com/FNC/GQV2/KX4OUXRC/FNCGQV2KX4OUXRC.jpg?auto=webp&fit=bounds&frame=1auto=webp&frame=1&height=300&auto=webp&fit=bounds&width=600&height=450&quality=75' alt='3. Removing Tea Stains' loading='lazy'></figure><figure><img src='https://content.instructables.com/F2C/IPMB/KX4OUXRD/F2CIPMBKX4OUXRD.jpg?auto=webp&fit=bounds&frame=1auto=webp&frame=1&height=300&auto=webp&fit=bounds&width=600&height=450&quality=75' alt='3. Removing Tea Stains' loading='lazy'></figure></div><p><strong>Étapes :</strong></p><ol><li>Tea - black tea especially - tends to leave stains on the inside of the mugs, that even the dishwasher fails to remove. If you ever had such an issue, salt is the answer. Place a teaspoon of salt on a sponge, give the mug a good rub and rinse.</li></ol>",
